##The prisons in Sichuan and Heilongjiang provinces entered a state of wartime administration

![img](data:image/jpeg;base64,)
Image: Visual China

The provinces of Sichuan and Heilongjiang have declared war-time prison management after it was revealed that five prisons in three provinces were infected with the virus.

According to the Wechat Bulletin of the Sichuan Provincial Department of Justice, on February 22, in response to the next step of the epidemic prevention and control work, the Department of Justice clearly requested that prison drug rehabilitation centers throughout the province implement wartime management and implement wartime discipline, and deeply understand the political nature and particularity of epidemic prevention in prison, strict defense, make every effort to ensure the safety of personnel, solid defense line. We will resolutely eliminate loopholes in the management of epidemic situations in prisons and spare no effort to prevent epidemic situations from spreading to prisons.

Sources said that since the outbreak of the new crown pneumonia, the Sichuan Provincial Department of Justice has attached great importance to the prevention and control of the epidemic situation, especially the epidemic prevention and control in the prison, and has rapidly implemented the full closed management of the prison, implementation of the "four-one rule" : All newly admitted criminals, drug addicts and persons who have left prison to visit relatives or return to prison are to be isolated, and all those who enter the drug rehabilitation facilities in prison are to have their temperature measured and wear face masks, to the body temperature excessively high or other suspected personnel all prohibit to enter and according to the stipulation disposal, to enters the prison the vehicle, the material all examination disinfection;

At the same time, "six suspensions" shall be implemented: All foreign personnel shall be suspended from entering the supervision area, including the non-supervision area where the police on duty shall not be allowed to enter the supervision area, face-to-face meetings and visits shall be suspended, and the transfer of drug addicts shall be suspended, there will be a temporary suspension of arraignment, family help, education and warning, as well as a temporary suspension of group meals for prisoners and drug addicts, and a suspension of all major activities in the prison.

Earlier, on February 21, the Sichuan Provincial Department of Justice organized and convened the Provincial Prison Drug Rehabilitation System Epidemic Prevention and control dispatching meeting and thirteen meetings of the department's Prevention and Control Leading Group. It was stressed that the surveillance video of all prisons since January 22 should be immediately sealed, organize prisons and drug rehabilitation centers to carry out cross-checks. If any problems are found in the checks, the relevant units and the persons responsible shall be dealt with seriously.

According to the Heilongjiang Daily News, the reporter learned from the Heilongjiang Department of Justice that from the 22nd, the prison drug rehabilitation facilities in the province entered the state of wartime management, resolutely plug the loopholes in epidemic prevention and control, to ensure "zero input, zero infection, zero speculation" goal.

According to reports, the Heilongjiang Department of Justice issued the epidemic prevention and control of wartime management, requiring closed doors, guards, intelligence, diligent cleansing, strict protection, early detection, decentralized, joint prevention and control, strict accountability.

At a press conference held by the Joint Prevention and Control Mechanism of the State Council on February 21, He Ping, head of the Prison Administration Bureau of the Ministry of Justice, said he felt guilty and heavy about the situation of prisoners infected with the epidemic. As of 2400 hours on February 20, a total of 5 prisons in Hubei, Shandong and Zhejiang provinces had reported cases of criminal infection, all of which were imported cases. Since the outbreak of the new pneumonia, all patients diagnosed in the prison system have been sent for diagnosis and treatment.

On February 22, Politburo member of the Communist Party of China and Secretary of the CPC Central Political and Legislative Committee Guo Shengkun stressed the importance of drawing lessons from the outbreak of an epidemic in individual regulatory sites during a surprise inspection of the epidemic prevention and control work in regulatory sites, we will resolutely put an end to paralysis, laxity and fluky mentality, and take extraordinary measures and wartime measures to contain the spread of the epidemic.
